Awka – Nnamdi Kanu, leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPOB), has said that Igbo leaders targeted for attack in foreign countries had orchestrated the death of over 600 of his members through ‘Operation Python Dance’ and allowed the desecration of Igbo tradition and culture when federal troop invaded his father’s compound. In a statement titled, ‘Setting the Record Straight’, on the activities of the leaders mentioned, Kanu reproduced the communiqué issued by the leaders which called for the proscription of IPOB. He said they also wanted him dead. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network He wrote: “These men instigated, financed, and defended a full-scale bloody military invasion of Biafraland they tagged ‘Operation Python Dance’ that led to the torture and untimely death of over 600 Biafrans, 28 of which fell in my compound. “These men sanctioned the desecration of the home of an Igbo traditional ruler by Fulani soldiers and did not care if my father, HRM Eze Israel Okwu Kanu, and my mother, who were home with me during the unprovoked invasion, was killed or not. “All these desperate Igbo politicians ever wanted was my death, the death of IPOB, the death of our dream of freedom for all. “In view of the Nuremberg encounter, it has become necessary for us to refresh our memories lest they succumb to confusion and deliberate misinformation, because most people, unlike we, IPOB, are in the habit of excusing intolerable evil and wickedness but we are not. “Every perpetrator of evil, every purveyor of iniquity, every merchant of misery, and every defender of injustice must and will be held to account. We will not relent until justice is served.”